1C pass 1H pass 1S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "a56a373031641c0ebc412a6887383e859cd34e1b762dcf01668166c519512760"]
[Category "Basic Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "basic_bidding/minor_suit_openings"]
[Student "S"]
{When you have two 4-card suits to show you bid them "up-the-line". In this case it means you say 1\H. Partner replies 1\S.  

There are enough points for game and a known 8-card Major fit. So you bid 4\S.

Perfect bidding isn't always rewarded. They can win three \D tricks and the Ace of trumps. If the opening lead is a \H or a \C you might make it, so it just depends on luck.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:KT4.J97.AK72.K53 Q62.Q42.43.QJT87 AJ5.KT6.Q986.A96 9873.A853.JT5.42"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1D pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "d372841fd5a548e83265cb58f01e158bef6addd6c1f7efacc9fbd5d9aaa94569"]
[Category "Basic Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "basic_bidding/minor_suit_openings"]
[Student "S"]
{You have two very good choices, neither of which is really wrong. You could bid 2NT, showing 13-16 points, balanced, or you could bid 3\D, showing 13-16 points, good trump support.

What should decide you is the bidding priorities. You'd much rather try to play a 9-trick game than an 11-trick game. And at the same time you must trust your partner not to leave you hung out in Notrump with an unsuitable hand. (Can you believe I wrote Notrump and unsuitable in the same sentence?)

Anyway, you bid 2NT and partner raises to 3NT.}

